### Solution

```lean
lemma dLpNorm_mul_le (p q : ÔäŁÔëą0Ôł×) (hrÔéÇ : r Ôëá 0) [hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r] :
    ÔÇľf * gÔÇľ_[r] ÔëĄ ÔÇľfÔÇľ_[p] * ÔÇľgÔÇľ_[q] := by
  obtain rfl | p := p
  ┬Ě sorry
  obtain rfl | q := q
  ┬Ě sorry
  obtain rfl | r := r
  ┬Ě sorry
  -- The following two come from `HolderTriple p q r`
  have hpÔéÇ : p Ôëá 0 := by
    simp_all [ENNReal.ne_zero]
    <;> aesop
  have hqÔéÇ : q Ôëá 0 := by
    simp_all [ENNReal.ne_zero]
    <;> aesop
  sorry
``` 

### Key Observations 
1. The last two lines of the proof are exactly the lines where the assumptions `hpÔéÇ : p Ôëá 0` and `hqÔéÇ : q Ôëá 0` are introduced. 
2. The fact that `q Ôëá 0` can be deduced from `hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple (some p) (some q) (some r)` because `p`, `q`, and `r` are positive, and `r Ôëá 0`. 
